# Astro / Performance / SEO Rules

- Core SEO content must render as static HTML.
- Do not depend on client-side JS for H1, service copy, city copy, internal links, reviews, FAQs, or CTAs.
- Use `.astro` components by default.
- Use JS only for progressive enhancement.
- Avoid React unless specifically approved.
- Avoid heavy npm packages.
- Every generated page should support:
  - SEO title
  - meta description
  - canonical URL
  - Open Graph image
  - H1
  - internal links
  - relevant CTA
- Use semantic HTML.
- Optimize images and include alt text.
